   People cool off at the Ebisugawa stepping stones that cross the Kamogawa River.
</p>

<p class="jp">
鴨川に架かる夷川飛び石で、人々が涼んでいる。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Kamo River" /><category term="Golden Hour" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[People cool off at the Ebisugawa stepping stones that cross the Kamogawa River.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2507_DSCF1151.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2507_DSCF1151.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Tenryuji Temple・天龍寺</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250630/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Tenryuji Temple・天龍寺" /><published>2025-06-30T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-06-30T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/tenryuji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250630/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
The grand gate of Tenryu-ji Temple at dusk.
</p>

<p class="jp">
夕暮れの天龍寺の総門。

</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Tenryu-ji" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The grand gate of Tenryu-ji Temple at dusk.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSCF1144_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSCF1144_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Crossing the Yodo River・淀川を渡る</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250629/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Crossing the Yodo River・淀川を渡る" /><published>2025-06-29T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-06-29T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/yodogawa</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250629/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Closeup on a Hankyu train as it crosses Osaka's Yodogawa River north of Umeda Station. It's an interesting location, where there are six tracks on three independent bridges next to each other. Below is a wider view of the Umeda skyline.
</p>

<p class="jp">
梅田駅の北、淀川を渡る阪急電車のクローズアップ。3つの独立した橋に6本の線路が並んでいる、興味深い場所だ。以下は、梅田のスカイラインのより広い景色だ。
</p>

<div class="subimagegroup">
   <img src="/assets/images/2025/2506_A7R05701-Pano.jpg"/>   
</div>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Osaka" /><category term="Trains" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Closeup on a Hankyu train as it crosses Osaka's Yodogawa River north of Umeda Station. It's an interesting location, where there are six tracks on three independent bridges next to each other. Below is a wider view of the Umeda skyline.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_A7R05742.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_A7R05742.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Baseballs・野球ボール</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250628/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Baseballs・野球ボール" /><published>2025-06-28T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-06-28T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/baseballs</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250628/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Baseballs at Shiramine Shrine, offered  - in gratitude for winning -  to the deity of ball sports enshrined here. Many soccer balls too...
</p>

<p class="jp">
白峰神社にある野球ボール。勝利の感謝を込めて、ここに祀られている球技の神様に奉納されたものだ。サッカーボールもある...
</p>
<p class="en">
Shot on Harman Phoenix 200 film and processed in Negative Lab Pro.
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Sports" /><category term="Shrines" /><category term="Film" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Baseballs at Shiramine Shrine, offered - in gratitude for winning - to the deity of ball sports enshrined here. Many soccer balls too...]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSC_0760-positive.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSC_0760-positive.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Togetsukyo Afternoon・渡月橋の午後</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250627/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Togetsukyo Afternoon・渡月橋の午後" /><published>2025-06-27T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-06-27T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/golden-togetsukyo</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250627/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
A telephoto lens compresses this late afternoon view of the Togetsukyo bridge  and the foliage of Mt. Arashi.
</p>

<p class="jp">
望遠レンズが、夕方の渡月橋と嵐山の紅葉を圧縮して映し出している。

</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Foliage" /><category term="Togetsu Bridge" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A telephoto lens compresses this late afternoon view of the Togetsukyo bridge and the foliage of Mt. Arashi.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSC_0711_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSC_0711_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Green Season・緑の季節</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250626/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Green Season・緑の季節" /><published>2025-06-26T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-06-26T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/green-season</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250626/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
The rain this time of year makes everything a lush shade of green.
</p>

<p class="jp">
この季節、雨で全てが青々とした緑色に染まる。

</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Foliage" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The rain this time of year makes everything a lush shade of green.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSC_0682_ai-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSC_0682_ai-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Kameyama-ya・亀山屋</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250625/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Kameyama-ya・亀山屋" /><published>2025-06-25T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-06-25T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kamyamaya</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250625/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
On my morning walk along the Oigawa river before this soba and oden restaurant  opened. It had just stopped raining, so the  sky was dark and the air was thick with moisture.
</p>

<p class="jp">
この蕎麦とおでんの老舗がまだ開店前の、大堰川沿いの朝の散歩道。雨上がりで空は暗く、しっとりとした空気に包まれていた。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Katsura River" /><category term="Rain" /><category term="Morning" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[On my morning walk along the Oigawa river before this soba and oden restaurant opened. It had just stopped raining, so the sky was dark and the air was thick with moisture.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSC_0674.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSC_0674.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Along the River</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250623/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Along the River" /><published>2025-06-23T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-06-23T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/yusai</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250623/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Women on the path along  the Oi River.
</p>

<p class="jp">
 大堰川沿いの道を行く女性たち。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Katsura River" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Women on the path along the Oi River.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_A7R05641.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_A7R05641.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Art Reflection・芸術的反映</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250622/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Art Reflection・芸術的反映" /><published>2025-06-22T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-06-22T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kyocera</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250622/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
    The Kyoto City Kyocera Museum is reflected in the glass windows of The Triangle building at left.
</p>

<p class="jp">
左側の「ザ・トライアングル」建物のガラス窓に、京都市京セラ美術館が映っている。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Higashiyama" /><category term="Museums" /><category term="Architecture" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The Kyoto City Kyocera Museum is reflected in the glass windows of The Triangle building at left.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSC_0660_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSC_0660_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Arriving Train・着く電車</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250621/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Arriving Train・着く電車" /><published>2025-06-21T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-06-21T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/train</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250621/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
     A long exposure transforms the arriving train at Hankyu’s Kami Katsura Station into a blur of light and shadow.
</p>

<p class="jp">
長時間の露出により、阪急「上桂駅」に到着する電車が、光と影のぼやけた姿に変貌した。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Trains" /><category term="Long Exposure" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A long exposure transforms the arriving train at Hankyu’s Kami Katsura Station into a blur of light and shadow.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_A7R05578-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_A7R05578-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry></feed>